8.5.1

A bag contains \(K\) blue balls and \(N âˆ’ K\) red balls. If \(n\) balls are randomly taken from the bag and denote number of blue balls as \(X\), prove that:

\[E[X] = n\frac{K}{N}\]

Proof

\(\sum_{k=0}^n k\frac{\binom{K}{k}\binom{N-K}{n-k}}{\binom{N}{n}}\)

\(=\frac{K}{\binom{N}{n}}\sum_{k=1}^n \binom{K-1}{k-1}\binom{N-K}{n-k}\)

\(=\frac{K}{\binom{N}{n}}\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} \binom{K-1}{k}\binom{N-K}{n-1-k}\)

\(=\frac{K}{\binom{N}{n}}\binom{N-1}{n-1}\)

\(=n\frac{K}{N}\)

Also

\[V(X)=n\frac{K}{N}\frac{N-K}{N}\frac{N-n}{N-1}\]
